        {
            "title": "德國企業信心意外升至2022年來最高",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"540\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/fKyJJDl4xJylHnwLczpIDg--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU0MDtjZj13ZWJw/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/b9435c6ef275eb82173276c0cb447b6e\" width=\"960\"/></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><br/></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 德國企業信心意外升至2022年以來的最高水平，此前歐盟與美國達成貿易協議，儘管有人批評關稅較高。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Ifo Institute的一項預期指數從7月修正後的90.8升至8月的91.6。彭博調查的經濟學家此前則預期下跌。一項衡量當前狀況的指標略有惡化。</p><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\" \" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"540\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/1IsNE60zK_rq405L.xtrog--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU0MDtjZj13ZWJw/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/18030a9e7d2c6ca13477c20969341469\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\"> </figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">「德國企業情緒已略有好轉，」Ifo總裁Clemens Fuest周一在一份聲明中表示。但他警告稱，「經濟復甦依然疲軟」。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">這項調查給德國帶來了復甦的希望，該國在俄烏戰爭後經歷了兩年的衰退。標準普爾全球8月綜合採購經理人指數顯示，歐洲最大經濟體的私營部門活動意外加速。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">推薦閱讀：德國第二季度GDP被下修 萎縮幅度超過最初估計</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題German Business Outlook Unexpectedly Hits Highest Since 2022</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">--聯合報導 Kristian Siedenburg、Harumi Ichikura、Joel Rinneby.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2025 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E5%BE%B7%E5%9C%8B%E4%BC%81%E6%A5%AD%E4%BF%A1%E5%BF%83%E6%84%8F%E5%A4%96%E5%8D%87%E8%87%B32022%E5%B9%B4%E4%BE%86%E6%9C%80%E9%AB%98-092249778.html",
